      • main

        public static void main(String[] args)
        Main method for SchoolManagerApp, fetches the arguments from Application @{code String[] args} calling the setLocale method and assigns SchoolModel schoolModel the instance of the model
        Parameters:
        args - two arguments are required when calling the application, by this order: 1st - language; 2nd - country

      • setLocale

        private static void setLocale(String[] args)
        This method reads the arguments from program arguments String[] args and set's the Localization Locale based on those arguments. If no arguments are given when calling the program, default will be set to language = en (English) Country = US (United States of America)
        Parameters:
        args - two arguments are required when calling the application, by this order: 1st - language; 2nd - country
        See Also:
        Locale
